          .container.mt55
            .row
              .col-sm-12
                p.fs18.
                  
                  The linear economy is traditionally managed on high margins generated by pollutive standardized end-products.
                  
                p.fs18.
                  
                  Our innovative circular economy model is based on tokenization of digital services dedicated to the textile value-chain interested to participate in the profits generated by online sales volume
                  
          .col-sm-12.mb30
            .image.mask-skew.wow.fadeIn(data-wow-offset='150' data-wow-duration='0.2s' data-wow-delay='.3s')
              .mask.wow.slideInLeft(data-wow-offset='150' data-wow-duration='1.2s' data-wow-delay='.3s')
                .inside
              img.img-fluid(src='img/pic159.jpg' alt)
      .container.mt55
        .row
          .col-sm-12
            p.fs18.
              
              The Naturaldyers proposal aims to divulge a disruptive information technology instrument that can provide dynamic data by sharing profits with the global community involved in eco-sustainability principles. The method allows rationalizing territorial GDP related to available natural resources connected with add value generated by involved textile value-chain to guarantee the actual value of a decentralized commercial token able to manage richness in the world in line with existing territorial excellencies and their demand on the market.
              
